<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,1083,1613]" box="[199,1236,1191,1218]" pageId="2" pageNumber="129">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,335,1192,1218]" pageId="2" pageNumber="129">Etymology.</emphasis>
The specific epithet refers to the sclerotized basal margin of the male paraproct.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="129" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,1083,1613]" pageId="2" pageNumber="129">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,322,1227,1254]" pageId="2" pageNumber="129">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
The new species is similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Stark &amp; Sivec, 2008" authorityName="Stark &amp; Sivec" authorityYear="2008" box="[672,991,1227,1254]" class="Insecta" family="Perlidae" genus="Flavoperla" kingdom="Animalia" order="Plecoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="129" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dao">
<emphasis box="[672,747,1227,1253]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="129">F. dao</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Stark, B. P. &amp; Sivec, I." box="[756,991,1227,1254]" pageId="2" pageNumber="129" pagination="59 - 65" refId="ref3374" refString="Stark, B. P. &amp; Sivec, I. (2008) New Vietnamese species of the genus Flavoperla Chu (Plecoptera: Perlidae). Illiesia, 4 (5), 59 - 65." type="journal article" year="2008">Stark &amp; Sivec, 2008</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Stark &amp; Sivec, 2008" authorityName="Stark &amp; Sivec" authorityYear="2008" box="[1004,1354,1227,1254]" class="Insecta" family="Perlidae" genus="Flavoperla" kingdom="Animalia" order="Plecoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="129" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hmong">
<emphasis box="[1004,1113,1227,1253]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="129">F. hmong</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Stark, B. P. &amp; Sivec, I." box="[1122,1354,1227,1254]" pageId="2" pageNumber="129" pagination="59 - 65" refId="ref3374" refString="Stark, B. P. &amp; Sivec, I. (2008) New Vietnamese species of the genus Flavoperla Chu (Plecoptera: Perlidae). Illiesia, 4 (5), 59 - 65." type="journal article" year="2008">Stark &amp; Sivec, 2008</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Stark &amp; Sivec, 2008" authorityName="Stark &amp; Sivec" authorityYear="2008" class="Insecta" family="Perlidae" genus="Flavoperla" kingdom="Animalia" order="Plecoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="129" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pallida">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="129">F. pallida</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Stark, B. P. &amp; Sivec, I." box="[238,468,1263,1290]" pageId="2" pageNumber="129" pagination="59 - 65" refId="ref3374" refString="Stark, B. P. &amp; Sivec, I. (2008) New Vietnamese species of the genus Flavoperla Chu (Plecoptera: Perlidae). Illiesia, 4 (5), 59 - 65." type="journal article" year="2008">Stark &amp; Sivec, 2008</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingCountry box="[538,637,1263,1289]" name="Vietnam" pageId="2" pageNumber="129">Vietnam</collectingCountry>
, but the male can be distinguished from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Stark &amp; Sivec" authorityYear="2008" box="[1098,1172,1263,1289]" class="Insecta" family="Perlidae" genus="Flavoperla" kingdom="Animalia" order="Plecoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="129" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dao">
<emphasis box="[1098,1172,1263,1289]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="129">F. dao</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the larger spines on tergum 10, the basolaterally sclerotized paraprocts, and by the much larger, laterally boot-shaped hammer (see figs. 
<quantity box="[151,222,1335,1362]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.62" metricValueMax="10.16" metricValueMin="5.08" pageId="2" pageNumber="129" unit="in" value="3.0" valueMax="4.0" valueMin="2.0">2–4 in</quantity>
<bibRefCitation author="Stark, B. P. &amp; Sivec, I." box="[228,452,1335,1362]" pageId="2" pageNumber="129" pagination="59 - 65" refId="ref3374" refString="Stark, B. P. &amp; Sivec, I. (2008) New Vietnamese species of the genus Flavoperla Chu (Plecoptera: Perlidae). Illiesia, 4 (5), 59 - 65." type="journal article" year="2008">Stark &amp; Sivec 2008</bibRefCitation>
). Males of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Chen" authorityYear="2019" box="[575,776,1335,1361]" class="Insecta" family="Perlidae" genus="Flavoperla" kingdom="Animalia" order="Plecoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="129" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="basomarginata">
<emphasis box="[575,776,1335,1361]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="129">F. basomarginata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be separated from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Stark &amp; Sivec" authorityYear="2008" box="[1034,1141,1335,1361]" class="Insecta" family="Perlidae" genus="Flavoperla" kingdom="Animalia" order="Plecoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="129" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hmong">
<emphasis box="[1034,1141,1335,1361]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="129">F. hmong</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the unpigmented head, the butterfly-shaped epiproct sclerite, and by the shorter basal stem of the hammer (see figs. 
<quantity box="[1198,1270,1371,1397]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.905" metricValueMax="2.286" metricValueMin="1.524" pageId="2" pageNumber="129" unit="in" value="7.5" valueMax="9.0" valueMin="6.0">6–9 in</quantity>
<bibRefCitation author="Stark, B. P. &amp; Sivec, I." pageId="2" pageNumber="129" pagination="59 - 65" refId="ref3374" refString="Stark, B. P. &amp; Sivec, I. (2008) New Vietnamese species of the genus Flavoperla Chu (Plecoptera: Perlidae). Illiesia, 4 (5), 59 - 65." type="journal article" year="2008">Stark &amp; Sivec 2008</bibRefCitation>
). The new species can also be separated in the male from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Stark &amp; Sivec" authorityYear="2008" box="[880,992,1407,1433]" class="Insecta" family="Perlidae" genus="Flavoperla" kingdom="Animalia" order="Plecoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="129" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pallida">
<emphasis box="[880,992,1407,1433]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="129">F. pallida</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the larger spines on tergum 10, the butterfly-shaped epiproct sclerite, the much larger, boot-shaped hammer, and by the unmodified female subgenital plate (see figs. 
<quantity box="[318,416,1479,1506]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.429" metricValueMax="3.81" metricValueMin="3.048" pageId="2" pageNumber="129" unit="in" value="13.5" valueMax="15.0" valueMin="12.0">12–15 in</quantity>
<bibRefCitation author="Stark, B. P. &amp; Sivec, I." box="[422,644,1479,1506]" pageId="2" pageNumber="129" pagination="59 - 65" refId="ref3374" refString="Stark, B. P. &amp; Sivec, I. (2008) New Vietnamese species of the genus Flavoperla Chu (Plecoptera: Perlidae). Illiesia, 4 (5), 59 - 65." type="journal article" year="2008">Stark &amp; Sivec 2008</bibRefCitation>
). The following key can be used to separate the known males of species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Chu" authorityYear="1929" box="[184,308,1515,1541]" class="Insecta" family="Perlidae" genus="Flavoperla" kingdom="Animalia" order="Plecoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="129" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[184,308,1515,1541]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="129">Flavoperla</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The aedeagus of the new species appears different from that of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Stark &amp; Sivec" authorityYear="2008" box="[1056,1168,1515,1541]" class="Insecta" family="Perlidae" genus="Flavoperla" kingdom="Animalia" order="Plecoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="129" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pallida">
<emphasis box="[1056,1168,1515,1541]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="129">F. pallida</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(see fig. 
<quantity box="[1279,1338,1515,1541]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.064" pageId="2" pageNumber="129" unit="in" value="16.0">16 in</quantity>
<bibRefCitation author="Stark, B. P. &amp; Sivec, I." pageId="2" pageNumber="129" pagination="59 - 65" refId="ref3374" refString="Stark, B. P. &amp; Sivec, I. (2008) New Vietnamese species of the genus Flavoperla Chu (Plecoptera: Perlidae). Illiesia, 4 (5), 59 - 65." type="journal article" year="2008">Stark &amp; Sivec 2008</bibRefCitation>
). However, comparison of aedeagi among all 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Chu" authorityYear="1929" box="[798,922,1551,1577]" class="Insecta" family="Perlidae" genus="Flavoperla" kingdom="Animalia" order="Plecoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="129" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[798,922,1551,1577]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="129">Flavoperla</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species is currently impossible due to lack of comparable data.
